6. Benefits of this MVP structure
● Zero direct DB — all state (products/orders) lives in Airtable.
● Make.com acts as your orchestrator (you can visually modify flows).
● Webhooks decouple your backend; no need to redeploy for DB schema tweaks.
● Frontend stays unchanged; it just renders what comes from Make.
● Future-proof — easily switch to real Postgres or Neon later by replacing
/api/make/* with DB calls.
